  <h1>Comparative Genomics of <i>Streptomyces silvae</i></h1>

  <p>
    The analysis includes two newly sequenced soil isolates and several publicly available genomes.
  </p>

  <h2>Dataset</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><i>Streptomyces silvae</i> TMS4I1</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces silvae</i> TMS12I2</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces silvae</i> For3T</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces</i> sp. M3</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces</i> sp. gb1(2016)</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces</i> sp. ADI93-02</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces</i> sp. SID4921</li>
    <li><i>Streptomyces</i> sp. LamerLS-316</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Methods</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>FastQC</li>
    <li>Trim Galore!</li>
    <li>Trimmomatic</li>
    <li>Unicycler</li>
    <li>Bowtie2</li>
    <li>Pilon</li>
    <li>RagTag</li>
    <li>RASTtk</li>
    <li>FastANI</li>
    <li>Mauve</li>
    <li>antiSMASH</li>
    <li>BUSCO</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>
    Comparative genome analysis included genome assembly, genome quality assessment,
    annotation, ANI comparisons, genome synteny analysis, and genome mining of biosynthetic gene clusters.
